-- China Agribank Applies for Lower Reserve Ratios, Observer Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-09-25T02:58:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-25/china-agribank-applies-for-lower-reserve-ratios-observer-says.html
Agricultural Bank of China Ltd.
applied to the central bank to lower the reserve ratio
requirement for its rural banking businesses, the Economic
Observer reported, citing unidentified officials. The bank is
seeking ratios of between 11 percent and 15 percent for more
than 2000 branches in rural areas, compared with a 17 percent
requirement on larger Chinese lenders at the moment, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yanping Li in Beijing at 
